wiki.summary: "I Didn't Change My Number" is a breakup song where Billie Eilish tells her ex that she's moved on and he should too. The song talks about how Billie changed who she replies to, indicating that she has cut off her ex from her life. Despite this, her ex still texts her, hoping to get a reaction out of her. The chorus serves as a warning to her ex that if he continues to bother her, she will become mean. In the second verse, Billie admits that her ex was attractive but warns that looks can be deceiving. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "I Didn't Change My Number" is a breakup song where Billie Eilish tells her ex that she's moved on and he should too. The song talks about how Billie changed who she replies to, indicating that she has cut off her ex from her life. Despite this, her ex still texts her, hoping to get a reaction out of her. The chorus serves as a warning to her ex that if he continues to bother her, she will become mean. In the second verse, Billie admits that her ex was attractive but warns that looks can be deceiving. She also mentions that she deserves better than to be hurt by him. The outro features repetition of "Mm-mm-mm", which adds to the emotional weight of the song and emphasizes that Billie has moved on and doesn't want to dwell on the past. Overall, "I Didn't Change My Number" is a message to Billie's ex that she has moved on and doesn't want to be bothered anymore. Read more on Last.fm.
